
Introduction
============

VEP2, (Visualizing Expression Platform2), a software for visualizing the gene expression in the single cell dataset.


Downloading page
================

https://github.com/xidan21/VEP2



Requirements 
============

Python 2.7 or higher


Installation
============

None


How to run ?
============

To run VEP2, start terminal to enter "$VEP2/bin/" and type:

python VEP


Input files
===========

1. Sequence matrix: a gene expression matrix, where the rows represent genes and the column represent samples.

2. Plot file: The corrdinates of tsne/uMAP plot.

3. Plot color file: the file containing the colors of each cell in the tsne/uMAP plot. 

